Invite your counselor to your Common App
Leave yourself a note or share one with your Team.

The essays tend to be one of the most laborious parts of the college application, so it's important to start early. Visit Columbia University's admissions website or log into your application account, find the topics, and think carefully about what you want to write about. Make sure that your voice comes through in your writing. If you're authentic and genuine, then you'll stand out from the crowd! Pay special attention to grammatical correctness and coherency so that your ideas and thoughts are communicated properly to your reader. Have a team member review it one last time before considering it done, then celebrate completing one of the most important tasks in your application process!
